DtHandler is a very basic datetime helper for django. 

Usage:
In [1]: import datetime

In [2]: dt = datetime.datetime(2010, 1, 1)

In [3]: from dthandler import DtHandler

In [4]: dth = DtHandler(dt)

In [5]: dth.localtime
Out[5]: datetime.datetime(2010, 1, 1, 0, 0, tzinfo=<DstTzInfo 'America/New_York' EST-1 day, 19:00:00 STD>)

In [6]: dth.utc
Out[6]: datetime.datetime(2010, 1, 1, 5, 0, tzinfo=<UTC>)

